\u00ebs 1485 [Defter of the Sanjak of Shkodra in 1485 |date=1974 |publisher=Academy of Sciences of Albania |page=99 |url=https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B3ma9plMXxAEZi1PZTVXMXV1NFE/edit |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite web |title=STUDIJA O OPRAVDANOSTI OSNIVANJA OP\u0160TINE GUSINJE |url=https://www.opstinagusinje.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/GUSINJE-studija.pdf |website=Opstina Gusinje |publisher=Gusinje Municipality |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|author=Zajednica osnovnog obrazovanja i vaspitanja|title=Simpozijum seoski dani Sretena Vukosavljevi\u0107a|volume=11|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7WJpAAAAMAAJ|year=1986|publisher=Op\u0161tinska zajednica obrazovanja|location=Prijepolje|ref=harv}}\n\n{{Gusinje Municipality}}\n{{MontenegroCities}}\n{{commons category|Gusinje}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gusinje}}\n[[Category:Populated places in Montenegro]]\n[[Category:Sand\u017eak]]\n[[Category:Plav, Montenegro]]\n", "name_user": "Maleschreiber", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMonuments", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gusinje"}
{"title_page": "Kam Zarf", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 Pakistani drama series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Kamzarf\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| native_name              = \n| genre                    = \n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| developer                = \n| writer                   = Seema Munaf\n| screenplay               = \n| story                    = \n| director                 = Zeeshan Ahmed\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = [[Junaid Khan (singer)|Junaid Khan]]<br> [[Nadia Khan]]<br>[[Rabab Hashim]]\n| narrated                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = [[Pakistan]]\n| language                 = Urdu\n| num_episodes             = 25\n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = Hassan Zia\n| location                 = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]]\n| cinematography           = \n| editor                   = \n| camera                   = [[Multi-camera setup]]\n| runtime                  = <!--Reliable source required-->\n| company                  = Mastermind Productions\n| distributor              = [[Geo TV]]\n| budget                   = \n| network                  = [[Geo Entertainment]]\n| picture_format           = [[PAL]] ([[576i]])<br>[[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format             = [[Stereophonic sound]]\n| first_run                = <!--The nation in which the series first aired, if different from country parameter-->\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|01|08|df=y}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|2019|06|11|df=y}}\n| preceded_by              = Meray Mohsin\n| followed_by              = \n| website                  = https://harpalgeo.tv/\n| production_website       = \n}}\n\n'''''Kamzarf''''' ({{Lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u06a9\u064e\u0645 \u0638\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0641}}|lit=Ungenerous}}) is a 2019 [[Pakistani dramas|Pakistani]] television series, produced by Hassan Zia under their production banner Mastermind Productions. It featured [[Junaid Khan (singer)|Junaid Khan]], [[Rabab Hashim]] and [[Nadia Khan]] in lead roles.\nThe drama aired weekly episode on [[Geo Entertainment]] every Tuesday from 8 January to 11 June 2019.<ref name=\"kamzarf\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/413830-upcoming-plays-of-2019|title=Upcoming plays of 2019|last=Desk|first=Instep|website=[[The News International]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/351265/four-episode-old-drama-serial-kamzarf-has-the-audience-on-the-edge-of-their-seats/|title=Four-episode old drama serial 'Kamzarf' has the audience on the edge of their seats|date=2019-02-04|website=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/19-Jun-2019/junaid-khan-and-rabab-prove-their-mettle-in-kamzarf|title=Junaid Khan and Rabab prove their mettle in Kamzarf|date=2019-06-18|website=[[The Nation (Pakistan)|The Nation]]|language=en|access-date=2019-06-23}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nStory of Aima ([[Nadia Khan]]), the eldest sister of her siblings Azhar ([[Junaid Khan (singer)|Junaid Khan]]), Asim ([[Ali Ansari (actor)|Ali Ansari]]) and Mona (Summaiya Bukhsh). Their parents died when she was 16 years old and she was left alone with her younger siblings, taking care of them as a mother, she wanted to marry her college friend but her father wanted her to take care of her siblings. Time lapse and she then appeared as an elderly women with her young siblings. Mona is still finishing her last semester, Azhar the second elder brother finds a girl ([[Nazish Jahangir]]) for himself and wanted to marry her but because of Aima's disagreements he couldn't and forced to married to a Tailor's daughter Fouzia ([[Rabab Hashim]]), whom he wasn't behaving really nice and quite harsh after marriage. Aima's uncle from America arrives, They have a young daughter Faria ([[Mariyam Nafees]]) who has a really liberal thought from which Asim is attracted to, so they decided to marry. Aima was also disagreeing to this marriage but Asim didn't listened, while Azhar formed a better relationship with his wife. While Aima meets his old love Nabeel ([[Alyy Khan]]), whom she wanted to marry, He is secretly married and has a child, he plans to marry Aima and take all her property, while Aima acting foolishly married him and gives him everything she had, while Faria, Asim's wife gets the house where the four siblings are living in form of a gift from her father, Aima opposes this decision and creates many misunderstandings in the house, while Mona founds a guy from University and they got married, Aima moves to Mona's house but couldn't live there more than two weeks she is left behind in a Woman's Asylum where the three siblings tried to find her but couldn't, because of Aima's unacceptable behavior and narrow-mindedness, she makes her life like hell and she was left alone at the end.\n\n==Cast== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Actor !! Character !! Notes\n|-\n| [[Junaid Khan (singer)|Junaid Khan]] \n| Azar\n| Fouzia's husband, Aima's younger brother, Mona and Asim's older brother<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/22-Feb-2019/rabab-junaid-taking-on-screen-chemistry-to-next-level|title=Rabab, Junaid taking on-screen chemistry to next level|date=2019-02-22|website=[[The Nation (Pakistan)|The Nation]]|language=en|access-date=2019-03-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Nadia Khan]]\n| Aima\n| Nabeel's second wife (later divorced by him) and Azar, Mona and Asim's older sister<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/341986/my-character-in-kam-zarf-is-negative-yet-pitiable-nadia-khan/|title=My character in 'Kam Zarf' is negative yet pitiable: Nadia Khan|date=2019-01-08|website=[[Daily Times (Pakistan)|Daily Times]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Rabab Hashim]]\n| Fouzia\n| Azar's wife, Safia's daughter<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/09-Jan-2019/rabab-to-make-a-comeback-with-kam-zarf|title=Rabab to make a comeback with \"Kam Zarf\"|date=2019-01-08|website=[[The Nation (Pakistan)|The Nation]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Mariyam Nafees]]\n| Faria\n| Aliyaan and Surya's daughter, Asim's wife<ref name=kamzarf1/>\n|-\n| Sumaiyya Bakhsh\n| Mona\n| Azar, Mona and Aima's younger sister, Noman's wife<ref name=kamzarf2>{{Cite web|url=https://gulfnews.com/entertainment/pakistani-cinema/junaid-khan-returns-with-new-show-kam-zarf-1.61289507|title=Junaid Khan returns with new show \u2018Kam Zarf\u2019|website=[[Gulf News]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Ali Ansari (actor)|Ali Ansari]]\n| Asim\n| Faria's husband, Azar and Aima's younger brother, Mona's older brother, Aliyaan's nephew<ref name=kamzarf2/>\n|-\n| [[Alyy Khan]]\n| Nabeel\n| Nazma's husband, Aima's husband (later divorced her)<ref name=kamzarf1>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/419186-geo-drama-kam-zarf-leads-on-chart|title=Geo Drama \u2018Kam Zarf\u2019 leads on chart|website=[[The News International]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n|-\n|Farah Nadeem\n| Surya\n| Aliyaan's wife, Faria's mother<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://harpalgeo.tv/program/Kamzarf|title=Kamzarf drama geo latest episode 11 June, 2019 - HarPal Geo.TV|website=[[Geo TV]]|access-date=2019-06-23}}</ref>\n|-\n| Sabiha Hashmi\n| Shazia\n|\n|-\n| Tauqeer Ahmed\n| Noman\n| Mona's husband\n|-\n|[[Nazish Jahangir]]\n| Nimra\n| Azar's love interest\n|-\n| Rubina Arif\n| Safia\n| Fouzia's mother\n|-\n| [[Arisha Razi]]\n| Aima (young)\n|\n|-\n| Aadi Khan\n| Nabeel (young)\n|\n|}\n\n==Production==\nThe series was earlier titled ''Kasa-e-Zaat'' but the makers changed it to ''Kam Zarf''.<ref name=kamzarf/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/411703-junaid-khan-on-his-next-kasa-e-zaat|title=Junaid Khan on his next, Kasa e Zaat|last=NewsBytes|website=[[The News International|The News]]|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Kam Zarf  - OST\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Shuja Haider]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|01|12}}\n| recorded   = 2019\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Television soundtrack]]\n| length     = (3:20)\n| language   = [[Urdu]]\n| label      = [[Geo TV]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{Youtube|PImXHefVpzI|\"Kam Zarf \" OST}}|type=song}}\n}}\nThe title song \" Na Baraf Na Pani\" was sung by [[Shuja Haider]]. The music was composed by [[Shuja Haider]] and the lyrics were written by Omaya Arif.Which has more than 1.5 Million views on [[YouTube]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://harpalgeo.tv Official website]\n\n[[Category:2019 Pakistani television series debuts]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 Pakistani drama series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Kamzarf\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| show_name_2              = \n| native_name              = \n| genre                    = \n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| developer                = \n| writer                   = Seema Munaf\n| screenplay               = \n| story                    = \n| director                 = Zeeshan Ahmed\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = [[Junaid Khan (singer)|Junaid Khan]]<br> [[Nadia Khan]]<br>[[Rabab Hashim]]\n| narrated                 = \n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country           